cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with distributed and streaming algorithms for solving the transshipment problem and approximate shortest paths. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves graph algorithms, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Networks and Networking). The use of gradient descent and randomized rounding suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
